</node>
<node id="Reticular Skeleton">
  <data key="d0">Reticular Skeleton</data>
  <data key="d1">anatomical_feature</data>
  <data key="d2">A spiky skeleton with soft tissue covering, characteristic of P. echinaster.&lt;SEP&gt;Reticular skeleton is an anatomical feature of Poraniopsis echinaster.&lt;SEP&gt;A spiky skeleton with soft tissue covering, characteristic of the described organism.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b7d87a9fdd6796fbc3a24c40022179ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83d371544d6eb48b5321717428ea68f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37cbd16434444d9480d8632be65be39c</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781097494</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Aboral Surface Spines">
  <data key="d0">Aboral Surface Spines</data>
  <data key="d1">anatomical_feature</data>
  <data key="d2">Distinct raised spines covering the aboral surface of P. echinaster, 1-4 mm in length.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b7d87a9fdd6796fbc3a24c40022179ca</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781095614</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tube Feet">
  <data key="d0">Tube Feet</data>
  <data key="d1">anatomical_feature</data>
  <data key="d2">The Thick Fleshy Starfish has double rows of tube feet.&lt;SEP&gt;Two rows of tube feet present in P. echinaster.&lt;SEP&gt;Double rows of tube feet on the Inflexible Rigid Star.&lt;SEP&gt;Double rows of tube feet present.&lt;SEP&gt;Two rows of tube feet present on the organism.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b7d87a9fdd6796fbc3a24c40022179ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c93021c72fb2fa03f2a5d62bc0adb874&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01224e247c54c26376338d1d355035dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c53974450202fe6a82416f946fc26f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37cbd16434444d9480d8632be65be39c</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781097488</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Madreporite">
  <data key="d0">Madreporite</data>
  <data key="d1">anatomical_feature</data>
  <data key="d2">The madreporite is distinct in the Thick Fleshy Starfish species.&lt;SEP&gt;White in colour, located off-centre halfway to the base of arms in P. echinaster.&lt;SEP&gt;Distinct madreporite of the Inflexible Rigid Star.&lt;SEP&gt;Distinct madreporite present.&lt;SEP&gt;White madreporite located offcentre halfway to base of arms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b7d87a9fdd6796fbc3a24c40022179ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c93021c72fb2fa03f2a5d62bc0adb874&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01224e247c54c26376338d1d355035dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c53974450202fe6a82416f946fc26f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37cbd16434444d9480d8632be65be39c</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781097488</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
