<node id="Luidia Africana">
  <data key="d0">Luidia Africana</data>
  <data key="d1">taxon</data>
  <data key="d2">Luidia africana is a starfish species with distinguishing features: arms that break off easily from the central disc, distinct spines on the aboral margin, long flexible flattened strap-like arms, usually five arms. Colour brown to dark pink. Size up to 150 mm diameter. Distribution: Southern African endemic, West and South Coasts of South Africa to Port Elizabeth, 54 m to 360+ m depth.&lt;SEP&gt;A distinct species or taxonomic entity mentioned as similar to Luidia sarsii africana, indicating potential synonymy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c93021c72fb2fa03f2a5d62bc0adb874&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0f7451703f2287af83a619489c9a745</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781097482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Astropecten Polyacanthus">
  <data key="d0">Astropecten Polyacanthus</data>
  <data key="d1">species</data>
  <data key="d2">Astropecten polyacanthus is a similar species to Luidia africana, with less flattened and broader arms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c93021c72fb2fa03f2a5d62bc0adb874</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781095626</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Astropecten Exilis">
  <data key="d0">Astropecten Exilis</data>
  <data key="d1">species</data>
  <data key="d2">Astropecten exilis is a similar species to Luidia africana, with less flattened and broader arms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c93021c72fb2fa03f2a5d62bc0adb874</data>
