<node id="Luidia sarsii africana taxonomic classification table (table)">
  <data key="d0">Luidia sarsii africana taxonomic classification table (table)</data>
  <data key="d1">table</data>
  <data key="d2">This table provides the full taxonomic hierarchy for Luidia sarsii africana (Legs break easily starfish), from Phylum Echinodermata through Class Asteroidea, Order Paxillosida, Family Luidiidae, Genus Luidia, to Species sarsii africana. Its common name directly reflects the species' fragile arms as described in the surrounding text. The classification supports identification and contextualizes the species within the guide to South African offshore marine invertebrates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0f7451703f2287af83a619489c9a745</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781096278</data>
</node>
