<node id="Spoladaster veneris taxonomic classification table (table)">
  <data key="d0">Spoladaster veneris taxonomic classification table (table)</data>
  <data key="d1">table</data>
  <data key="d2">This table provides the taxonomic hierarchy (Phylum to Species) and common name for the starfish Spoladaster veneris ('Inflated star'). It is placed within a field guide section that contrasts this species with two similar species (Chondraster ellatosis and Spoladaster brachyactis) based on inflation and leatheriness. The classification confirms its genus (Spoladaster) and distinguishes it from Chondraster, supporting the morphological comparisons in the surrounding text.</data>
