<node id="Echinodermata Distinguishing Anatomical Features">
  <data key="d0">Echinodermata Distinguishing Anatomical Features</data>
  <data key="d1">anatomical_feature</data>
  <data key="d2">A set of distinguishing features including short-armed stellate body, reticular skeleton, raised spines (1-4mm), rigid arms, two rows of tube feet, white madreporite off-centre, and strong spines at arm base.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5bd15d157743c89b7fd9be20dd1df380</data>
