<node id="Chondraster elattosis">
  <data key="d0">Chondraster elattosis</data>
  <data key="d1">species</data>
  <data key="d2">Chondraster elattosis is a starfish species known as Pentagon star, belonging to the family Poraniidae, with pentagonal body shape, cushion-like body, bright pink to orange aboral color, size up to 230 mm diameter, endemic to South Africa's West and South Coasts at depths 400 to 1000+ m.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c2277bdb0cfb9e13e612107b546b5702</data>
  <data key="d4">Field-Guide-to-SA-Offshore-Marine-Invertebrates_web-full-version_compressed.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1781097514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
